@startuml
title Utility Patterns - Practical Flow

skinparam classAttributeIconSize 0

class ObservableValue
class ContractProvider
class CachedData
class Flags
class ObjectPool
class BinaryField
class ThreadSafeDeque

class "Event listeners" as Listeners
class "Dirty render data" as DirtyData
class "Option sets" as Options
class "Reusable objects" as Objects
class "Cross-thread queues" as Queues

ObservableValue --> Listeners : notifies changes
ContractProvider --> Listeners : manages subscriptions
CachedData --> DirtyData : rebuilds on demand
Flags --> Options : stores named bits
ObjectPool --> Objects : reuses allocations
BinaryField --> Objects : exposes typed byte sections
ThreadSafeDeque --> Queues : passes work between loops

note bottom
Utility types appear throughout Sparkle where a small,
reusable behavior is clearer than duplicating local code.
end note

@enduml
